data.name: textBoxDescription.Text
data.value:
Description: Click on the particles as they rise up to earn points, if you click and miss, you'll lose a life, lose all three lifes and it's game over.
You can pause the game by pressing space
Both the left and right mouse buttons work
You can add your own custom fireworks by editting the sprites using the Edit Sprites Button from either the main menu, or the pause menu. You can use the New menu to either import an xml document containing coordinates for sprites or you can import bitmap images. When imported from a bitmap, a sprite's coordinates are determined by the location of black pixels on the image. Once imported the image will automatically begin appearing in the game. You can export the current sprites into an xml document using the export button, this can then be loaded into the editor at a later time if needed.
